  "words": "st. 1-2 by Sarah F. Adams, 1841. st. 3-5 by Hervey D. Ganse (1822-1891) st. 6 by Edward H. Bickersteth, Jr. (1825-1906)",
  "music": "Lowell Mason, 1856 Lowell Mason, 1859",
  "tune": "Bethany (Mason)",
  "lyrics": {
    "v1": "Nearer, my God, to Thee, nearer to Thee! E&#39;en though it be a cross that raiseth me, Still all my song shall be, nearer, my God, to Thee. Nearer, my God, to Thee, Nearer to Thee!",
    "v2": "Though like the wanderer, the sun gone down, Darkness be over me, my rest a stone. Yet in my dreams I&#39;d be nearer, my God to Thee. Then evermore to be Nearer to Thee!",
    "v3": "Nearer, my Lord, to thee, Nearer to thee! Who to the cross didst come, Dying for me! Strengthen my willing feet, Hold me in service sweet",
    "v4": "Nearer, O Comforter, Nearer to thee! Who with my loving Lord Dwellest with me! Grant me thy fellowship! Help me each day to keep",
    "v5": "But to be nearer still, Bring me, O God, Not by the visioned steeps Angels have trod. Here where thy cross I see, Jesus, I wait for thee,"
  },
